Privacy Policy
kamgam.com Privacy Policy - December 23rd, 2020
KAMGAM e.U., Linzerstraße 17, 4100 Ottensheim, Austria (“kamgam.com”)
Games, services and websites provided on the respective platform (“kamgam.com ' Services”, "Services")
If you are here to opt out of all data collection then please go
here
.
This Privacy Policy governs your use of kamgam.com and all the services that kamgam.com offers on the kamgam.com websites including the games and applications offered by KAMGAM and those accessed through third party web sites.
Privacy
Information collected from you on any third party website is subject to the pertinent third party’s policy. By use of our service, you may be granting your third party website (example: social network) permission to share your e-mail address and any other personally identifiable information with KAMGAM. If you do not agree, then you should either deny the requests presented to you at the first start of our service or not use KAMGAM services or not submit any personally identifiable information through them.
Cookies
KAMGAM may use “cookies” to store personal data on your computer. If it does it will show a "cookie banner" with more detailed settings. We may also link information stored on your computer in cookies with data about specific individuals stored on our servers (example: "remember me" feature of login forms). If you set up your web browser so that cookies are not allowed, you might not be able to use some or all of the features of KAMGAM's Services.
Logfiles
KAMGAM's Services may store data which is used to obtain technical and statistical information to improve the services.
Analytics in our applications
If you allowed data collection at the first start of our service you agreed to this data being collected and used for analytics. To that end KAMGAM may use third party solutions to improve the game and track certain data like player behaviour, error reports, location (based on IP address), game progress and device information (like os version, hardware model, your chosen language).
GADSME
KAMGAM may use the service of GADSME (http://gadsme.com) which is a company based in France (EU). By using our services you are also subject to their
privacy policy
. Please send any requests concerning deletion or correction of your analytics data directly to dpo@gadsme.com or follow the
opt out instructions
.
AppLovin
KAMGAM may use the service of AppLovin (https://www.applovin.com) which is a company based in California (USA). By using our services you are also subject to their
privacy policy
. Please send any requests concerning deletion or correction of your analytics data directly to dataprotection@applovin.com or follow the
opt out instructions
.
Unity Analytics
KAMGAM may use Unity Analytics (https://unity3d.com/solutions/analytics). Parts of their data collection may take place in the US which was covered by the
EU-US Privacy Shield
and is now operating under the SCC (EU Standard Contractual Clauses) as defined in GDPR Article 46 (2)(c). You can find out more on the Unity
privacy policy
pages. At the moment Unity Analytics does not offer an opt-out on a website. If you do not want your information collected then you need to either stop using the app or deny the request for analytics at the first start of the app (can be changed any time within the app). Please send any requests concerning deletion or correction of your data directly to DPO@unity3d.com or follow the
opt out instructions
Your rights according to the GDPR
Under the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) you have the right for information, correction, deletion, restriction, data portability, revocation and opposition. If you want to exercise your right under the GDPR then please contact us under office<AT>kamgam<DOT>com.
Data Collection Services & Opt-Out
Some, not all, maybe none of the following webservice may apply to you.
KAMGAM Games
Here you will find the data deletion instructions for our game(s).
Airborne Motocross
Airborne Motocross does not save any personal data. The only data that is saved is your progress in-game.
Even if you send a restore code to your e-mail address we will not save your e-mail. It is just used once to send the message and is not stored permanently.
However, the game serves ads through the Unity Ad network. To check how you can delete your data from their network please refer to the "Unity Analytics & UnityAds Opt-Out" section below.
If you have any questions or want your game related savegame data deleted please write to app-support@kamgam.com. Please mention your user id in your request. You can find it in the main menu (bottom left corner) right below the popup with the "Settings, Feedback ,.." buttons (the small grey font). It's the part that says "u:" followed by a 10 digit random combination.
Please notice that replies may take a few days. Thank you for your patience.
